/*Data for the table `predstave` */

insert  into `predstave`(`ID`,`Naziv`,`Naziv_en`,`Vrijeme_Pon`,`Vrijeme_Uto`,`Vrijeme_Sri`,`Vrijeme_Cet`,`Vrijeme_Pet`,`Cijena`,`Min_Opis_hr`,`Opis_hr`,`Radnja_hr`,`Uloge_hr`,`Min_Opis_en`,`Opis_en`,`Radnja_en`,`Uloge_en`) values (1,'Fantom u operi','The Phantom of the Opera','14:00:00','18:30:00','17:30:00','15:15:00','20:00:00','25 kuna','Mjuzikl Andrewa Lloyda Webbera nastao je na temelju romana Gastona Lerouxa \"The Phantom of the Opera\"','Mjuzikl Andrewa Lloyda Webbera nastao je na temelju romana Gastona Lerouxa The Phantom of the Opera i postao najprofitabilniji\r\nkazališni projekt na svijetu zaradivši više od 3.2 milijarde američkih dolara. Premijerno je prikazan u Her Majesty`s Theatre na\r\nlondonskom West Endu 9. listopada 1986. godine, a odonda ga je vidjelo više od 80 milijuna ljudi. Fantom u operi je izveden više od65 tisuća puta u 18 zemalja svijeta, nagrađen je s više od 50 nagrada, uključujući tri nagrade Olivier, sedam nagrada Tony,\r\nsedam nagrada Drama Desk i tri nagrade Outer Critic\'s Circle.','Radnja se zbiva krajem 19. stoljeća u velebnom zdanju zgrade pariške operne kuće. Nakon što mlada sopranistica Kristina postane\nnjen prvi glas, primjećuje ju novi patron, njen naočit prijatelj iz djetinjstva, Raoul vikont Chagny. No prisutnost treće osobe,\ntajanstvenog Fantoma, glazbenog genija i Kristininog “glazbenog anđela” skrivenog u dubinama katakomba Opere, uskoro dovodi mladi\ndvojac i ostale protagoniste u vrtlog strasti, opsjena i smrti.','Glavne uloge u ovoj koncertno-scenskoj inačici tumačit će izvrsni prokušani mladi interpretatori glavnih uloga sa londonske scene\nRamin Karimloo i Sierra Boggess, koji su osim u izvorniku iste likove uspješno odigrali i u Lloyd Webberovom scenskom nastavku\npriče o Fantomu “Ljubav nikad ne umire” (Love Never Dies).','The musical by Andrew Lloyd Webber was created based on the novel by Gaston Leroux, \'The Phantom of the Opera\'','The musical by Andrew Lloyd Webber was created based on the novel by Gaston Leroux, \'The Phantom of the Opera\' \nand became the most profitable theater project in the world, earning more than 3.2 billion US dollars. \nIt was first presented to Her Majesty`s Theatre on London\'s West End on October 9 1986, \nand since then it has been seen by more than 80 million people. \n\'Phantom of the Opera\' was performed more than 65,000 times in 18 countries around the world, \nhas been awarded with more than 50 awards, including three Olivier Awards, seven Tony Awards, \nseven Drama Desk awards and three awards Outer Critic\'s Circle.','The story takes place in the late 19th century in the magnificent building of the Paris opera house. After the young soprano \r\nKristina becomesher first voice, observes her new protector, her handsome childhood friend, Raoul Viscount Chagny. \r\nBut the presence of a third party, mysterious Phantom, musical genius and Cristina\'s angel of music hidden in the depths of the\r\ncatacombs of the Opera, soon leads young duo and other protagonists in the vortex of passion, illusion and death.','Leading roles in this concert-stage version shall be interpreted by excellent proven young performers from the London scene\r\nRamin Karimloo and Sierra Boggess, who in addition to the original play of the same characters successfully played in\r\nLloyd Webber\'s stage which follows the story of the Phantom \'Love never dies\''),(2,'Pepeljuga','Cinderella','16:45:00','12:00:00','20:30:00','24:00:00','16:00:00','10 kuna','Predstava na temelju istoimene bajke','Da li znate da postoji preko 300 inačica ove priče diljem svijeta, a najstarijoj je preko 2000 godina?\nOva je bajka nastala u različitim narodima. Tematski je vezana uz elemente nepravednog ugnjetavanja (postoji li uopće \npravedno ugnjetavanje?) /pravedne nagrade i svoju nam bezvremenost dokazuje već stoljećima. Danas nam je potrebna možda više no\nikad prije ne samo kao ukazatelj na rastući problem nasilja među mladima, već i kao podsjetnik na pomalo zaboravljene ljudske\nvrijednosti tolerancije, marljivosti i nadasve – ljubavi. Zahvaljujući svemu navedenome, „Pepeljuga“ zasluženo pronalazi svoje\nmjesto u svakome djetinjstvu.','Kralj je priredio dvorski bal i pozvao sve djevojke u kraljevstvu. Baš sve, da njegov princ odabere onu od čijega će mu pogleda\r\nuzdrhtati ravnodušno srce. Htjela je poći i Pepeljuga, sašila je sebi skromnu haljinu, umila se i začešljala kosu, ali su ju maćeha\r\ni njezine kćeri ismijale i ponizile, razderale joj haljinu i zapovijedile slugi da Pepeljugu ne pušta iz kuće. Bila je žalosna i\r\nnesretna... U tom trenutku u predstavi se pojavljuje dobra vila, ali ne vila koja se samo tako sažalila nad Pepeljugom, ne,\r\nta se vila bila jednom davno privremeno odrekla svog vilinskog svijeta i zaljubljena u mladoga trgovca odlučila živjeti među\r\nljudima. Nećemo otkriti što je vila Pepeljugi i što je Pepeljuga vili, to ćete saznati u predstavi. I doznat ćete zašto čarolije\r\ndobre vile imaju tako kratak rok, zašto Pepeljuga mora pobjeći s dvorskog plesa čim počne otkucavati ponoć – baš onda kada se\r\nrasplamsa ljubav između nje i princa. ','Pepeljuga: Karla Brbić\r\nPrinc: Jure Radnić\r\nKralj: Krunoslav Klabučar\r\nMaćeha, gospođa Malicioza: Vanda Vujanić Šušnjar\r\nDora : Daria Knez Rukavina\r\nLora: Marijana Mikulić\r\nBonvivan, kraljev savjetnik: Hrvoje Barišić\r\nVila: Tena Jeić Gajski\r\nSluga: Ranko Stojić','The play based on the fairy tale','Did you know that there are over 300 versions of the story around the world, and the oldest is more than 2000 years?\r\nThis is a fairy tale created in different nations. It is thematically related to the elements of unjust oppression\r\n(is there even right kind of oppression?) / Fair remuneration and its timelessness proves us for centuries. Today we need perhaps\r\nmore than ever before, not only as illustrate the growing problem of violence among young people, but also as a reminder of the\r\nsomewhat forgotten folk values of tolerance, hard work and above all - love. Thanks to all this, \'Cinderella\' deserved her place in\r\nevery childhood.','King has put the ball court and invited all the girls in the kingdom to choose one of whose views will startle his indifferent\r\nheart. Cinderella also wanted to go, she sewed herself a modest dress, washed her face and brushed back her hair,\r\nbut her stepmother and her daughters ridiculed and humiliated her, pierced her dress and ordered the servant to not let Cinderella out of the house. \r\nShe was sad and unfortunate. At this point in the play comes the good fairy, but not fairy who just took pitty on Cinderella,\r\nthat fairy fell in love with a young merchant and decided to live among humans. \r\nWe will not reveal who is the fairy to Cinderella and vice-versa, you will find that in the play. And you will find out why magic\r\nspells are so short term, why Cinderella has to escape from dance as soon as midnight - just when the love between\r\nher and the prince start growing.','Cinderella: Karl Brbić\r\nPrince: Jure Radnić\r\nKing: James Klabučar\r\nStepmother, Mrs. Malicioza: Vanda Vujanić Šušnjar\r\nDora: Daria Knez Rukavina\r\nLora: Marijana Mikulić\r\nBon vivant, the king\'s counselor: Hrvoje Barišić\r\nVilla: Tena Jeić Gajski\r\nValet: Ranko Stojić'),(3,'Romeo i Julia','Romeo and Juliet','18:00:00','13:30:00','22:30:00','12:45:00','17:30:00','40 kuna','Balet Romeo i Julija lirska je priča o tragičnim veronskim ljubavnicima','Balet Romeo i Julija lirska je priča o tragičnim veronskim ljubavnicima na glazbu Sergeja Sergejeviča Prokofjeva, koja je od\r\nsvojega nastanka 1938. godine neprekidno nadahnuće mnogih generacija koreografa i redatelja. To slavno baletno djelo nastalo je\r\nprema Shakespeareovoj drami Romeo i Julija, jednoj od najljepših, najtragičnijih i najčitanijih priča svjetske literature koja već četiri stoljeća služi kao nepresušni izvor inspiracije autorima različitih umjetničkih izričaja.','Monteki i Kapuleti su dvije zavađenje veronske obitelji. Na glavnom veronskom trgu izbija svađa koja završava kneževim upozorenjem.\r\nNaslućuje se da je Romeo zaljubljen u Rozalinu, djevojku iz roda Kapuletija. Glava porodice Kapuleti organizira zabavu, a Romeova\r\nljubav prema Rozalini navede ga da dođe na zabavu. Na zabavi Romeo susreće Juliju. Između njih se rađa čista i iskrena ljubav,\r\nbez ograničenja koja su nametnuta mržnjom između njihovih obitelji. Romea i Juliju tajno vjenča svećenik. Kapuletijev nećak Tibaldo\r\nu svađi ubija Merkucija, Romeovog prijatelja. Želeći osvetiti smrt svog dobrog prijatelja, Romeo ubija Tibalda. Zatim mora pobjeći,\r\njer uskoro dolazi knez. Preneražen prizorom, knez osuđuje Romea na progonstvo u Mantovu, ali njegovi osjećaji prema Juliji\r\nsprječavaju ga u tome i on se skriva kod franjevca Lorenca. Otac i majka žele Juliju udati za Parisa, uglednog i bogatog plemića.\r\nZbog vječne ljubavi na koju se zavjetovala udajom za Romea, ona radije izabere smrt nego udaju za Parisa. Fratar Lorenzo,\r\nželeći spriječiti tragediju, daje Juliji napitak koji bi je trebao uspavati, a šalje poruku Romeu da je ona zapravo živa.\r\nNažalost, glasnik ne dospijeva na vrijeme reći Romeu istinu zbog epidemije kuge koja je izolirala grad. On odlazi u grobnicu\r\nKapuletija i, misleći da mu život bez Julije više nema smisla, ispija otrov i umire. Neposredno nakon toga budi se Julija.\r\nVidjevši da joj se muž ubio, iz tuge uzima bodež i oduzima sebi život. Nakon tragedije u grobnicu dolaze ostali članovi dviju\r\nobitelji. Nad mrtvim tijelima njihove djece oni se mire.','Julija: Iva Vitić Gameiro\r\nRomeo: Andrea Schifano\r\nTibaldo: Guilherme Gameiro Alves\r\nGrofica Capuleti: Natalia Horsnell\r\nMercuzio: Tomislav Petranović\r\nBenvoglio: Takuya Sumitomo\r\nParis: Duilio Ingraffia\r\nGrof Capuleti: Azamat Nabiullin\r\nGrofica Montecchi: Milka Hribar Bartolović\r\nGrof Montecchi: Andrej Izmestjev\r\nRosalinda: Rieka Suzuki\r\nParisovi prijatelji: Kristian Manev, Ovidiu Muscalu / Duilio Ingraffia, Kornel Palinko, Dan Rus\r\nMercuziovi prijatelji: George Baldovin, Simon Yoshida / Eugen Dobrescu, Tomaž Golub\r\nJulijina dojilja: Martina Fici\r\nPater Lorenzo: Andrej Barbanov\r\nJulijine prijateljice: Catarina Meneses, Dunja Novković, Cristiana Rotolo, Valentina Štrok / Saya Ikegami, Asuka Maruo, \r\nRebecca Smith, Tammy Higgins, Catarina Meneses, Miruna Miciu, Rieka Suzuki, Atina Tanović /Daria Brdovnik Bukvić, Asuka Maruo,\r\nMutsumi Matsuhisa, Ozana Mirković, Simona Unterajter\r\nKraljica Mab: Tammy Higins, Mutsumi Matsuhisa, Miruna Miciu, Rieka Suzuki, Atina Tanović /Daria Brdovnik Bukvić, Rebecca Smith,\r\nPavla Pećušak, Simona Unterajter\r\nPrijatelji obitelji Montecchi: Catarina Meneses, Dunja Novković, Valentina Štrok / Saya Ikegamy, Asuka Mauro, Cristiana Rotolo,\r\nEugen Dobrescu, Ovidiu Muscalu, Dan Rus / Duilio Ingraffia, Sebastian Šimić, Simon Yoshida\r\nPrijatelji obitelji Capuleti: Gianmarco Beoni, Tomaž Golub, Adam Harris, Kristian Manev, Kornel Palinko / Sebastian Šimić,\r\nSimon Yoshida\r\nTibaldovi prijatelji: Siniša Bosnar, Ioan Dumitru Moga, Sebastian Šimić / Andrej Barbanov, Filip Filipović\r\nGosti na balu Capuletija: Tatjana Andročec, Ilinca Barbu Moga, Danijela Batur, Emilija Sorić, Bojana Suntešić,\r\nSimona Unterajter Dunja Zoričić /Saule Ashimova, Tatjana Hrvačić Gašparac, Sanda Miš, Barbara Novković Novak, Danijela Zobunđija,\r\nAndrej Barbanov, Siniša Bosnar, Ioan Dumitru Moga, Filip Filipović, Sebastian Šimić, Nicoale Vasc,\r\nDomagoj Vrbljanin /Gianmarco Beoni, Alen Gotal, Andrija Palada\r\nGrađani Verone: Daria Brdovnik Bukvić, Tammy Higins, Catarina Meneses, Dunja Novković, Cristiana Rotolo, Valentina Štrok,\r\nAtina Tanović /Saya Ikegami, Mutsumi Masuhisa, Asuka Maruo, Ozana Mirković, Emilija Sorić, Simona Unterajter, Gianmarco Beoni,\r\nTomaž Golub, Adam Harris, Kristian Manev, Ovidiu Muscalu, Kornel Palinko, Dan Rus /Andrej Barbanov, Sebastian Šimić, Dunja Zoričić\r\nKarneval: Daria Brdovnik Bukvić, Tammy Higgins, Catarina Meneses, Dunja Novković, Cristiana Rotolo, Valentina Štrok,\r\nAtina Tanović /Tatjana Andročec, Asuka Mauro, Mutsumi Matsuhisa, Emilija Sorić, Eugen Dobrescu, Tomaž Golub, Adam Harris,\r\nKristian Manev, Ovidiu Muscalu, Kornel Palinko, Siniša Bosnar /Andrej Barbanov, Gianmarco Beoni, Alen Gotal, Sebastian Šimić,\r\nIlinca Barba Mogu, Saya Ikegami, Ozana Mirković, Sanda Miš, Barbara Novković Novak, Rebecaa Smith, Danijela Zobunđija,\r\nDunja Zoričić, Tomaž Golub, Ioan Dumitru Moga, Filip Filipović','The ballet Romeo and Juliet is a lyrical story of the tragic Verona lovers','The ballet Romeo and Juliet is a lyrical story of the tragic Verona lovers to music by Sergei Sergeyevich Prokofiev, \nwhich since its inception in 1938 constant inspiration to many generations of choreographers and directors. \nThis famous ballet originates from Shakespeare\'s Romeo and Juliet, one of the most beautiful, the most tragic \nand the most read stories of world literature that has served as an inexhaustible source of inspiration \nfor authors of different artistic expressions.','Montagues and Capulets are two feuding Verona family. On the main square starts quarreling  which end with rector\'s warning.\r\nOne might guess that the Romeo in love with Rosaline, a girl from Capulets family.\r\nThe head of the family Capulets organized entertainment, and Romeo\'s love for Rosaline indicate him to come to the party. \r\nAt the party, Romeo meets Juliet. Among them is born pure and honest love, without restrictions imposed by hatred between \r\ntheir families. Romeo and Juliet then get secretly married by a priest.Capulet\'s nephew Tybalt in a quarrel kills Mercutio,\r\nRomeo\'s friend. Wanting to avenge the death of his good friend, Romeo kills Tybalt. Then he has to escape, because the prince is\r\ncoming soon. Stupefied by the sight, the prince condemns Romeo to exile in Mantua, but his feelings for Julia prevent it from\r\ndoing so, and goes into hidding. The father and mother want Julia to marry Paris, a prominent and wealthy nobleman.\r\nBecause of eternal love on which vowed and married Romeo, she would rather choose death than marry Paris. Friar Lorenzo,\r\nwanting to prevent the tragedy, gives Juliet a sleeping potion and sends a message to Romeo that she was actually alive.\r\nUnfortunately, the messenger is not due on time to tell Romeu the truth due to the plague that isolated the city.\r\nHe went to the Capulets grave and, referring to his life without sense without Juliet, drinks poison and dies.\r\nShortly thereafter Juliet wakes up. Seeing her husband killed, from grief she takes a dagger and takes her own life.\r\nAfter the tragedy to the grave comes the rest of the two family and they agree on the piece between them.','Juliet: Iva Vitić Gameiro\r\nRomeo: Andrea Schifano\r\nTybalt: Guilherme Gameiro Alves\r\nCountess Capuleti: Natalia Horsnell\r\nMercuzio: Tomislav Petranović\r\nBenvoglio: Takuya Sumitomo\r\nParis: Duilio Ingraffia\r\nCount Capuleti: Azamat Nabiullin\r\nCountess Montague: Milka Hribar Bartolović\r\nCount Montecchi: Andrej Izmestjev\r\nRosalind: Rieka Suzuki\r\nParis\'s friends: Kristian Manev, Ovidiu Muscalu / Duilio Ingraffia, Kornel Palinko, Dan Rus\r\nMercuz\'s friends: George Baldovin, Simon Yoshida / Eugen Dobrescu, Tomaz Golub\r\nJuliet\'s nurse: Martin Fici\r\nFather Lorenzo: Andrej Barbanov\r\nJulia\'s friends: Catarina Meneses, Dunja Novkovic, Cristiana Rotolo, Valentina Strok / Saya Ikegami, Asuka Maruo,\r\nRebecca Smith, Tammy Higgins, Catarina Meneses, Miruna Mici, Rieka Suzuki, Athens Tanovic / Daria BRDOVNIK Bukvic, Asuka Maruo,\r\nMutsumi Matsuhisa, Ozana Mirkovic, Simon Unterajter\r\nQueen Mab: Tammy Higgins, Mutsumi Matsuhisa, Miruna Mici, Rieka Suzuki, Athens Tanovic / Daria BRDOVNIK Bukvic, Rebecca Smith,\r\nPaul Pečušak, Simon Unterajter\r\nFriends of family Montecchi: Catarina Meneses, Dunja Novkovic, Valentina Strok / Saya Ikegamy, Asuka Mauro, Cristiana Rotolo,\r\nEugen Dobrescu Ovidiu Muscalu, Dan Rus / Duilio Ingraffia, Sebastian Simic, Simon Yoshida\r\nFriends of family Capuleti: Gianmarco Beoni, Tomaz Golub, Adam Harris, Kristian Manev, Kornel Palinko / Sebastian Simic,\r\nSimon Yoshida\r\nTibaldi\'s friends: Sinisa BOSNAR Ioan Dumitru Moga, Sebastian Simic / Andrej Barbanov, Filip Filipovic\r\nGuests at the ball Capuletija: Tatjana Andročec, Ilinca Barbu Moga, Danijela Batur, Emilia Sorić, Bojana Suntešić,\r\nSimon Unterajter Dunja Zoricic / Saule Ashimova, Tatjana Hrvačić Gašparac, Sanda Mouse, Barbara Novković Novak, Daniel Zobunđija,\r\nAndrej Barbanov, Sinisa BOSNAR Ioan Dumitru Moga, Filip Filipovic, Sebastian Simic, Nicoale Vasc.\r\nDomagoj Vrbljanin / Gianmarco Beoni, Alen Gotal, Andrew Pallas\r\nCitizens of Verona: Daria BRDOVNIK Bukvic, Tammy Higgins, Catarina Meneses, Dunja Novkovic, Cristiana Rotolo, Valentina Strok,\r\nAthens Tanovic / Saya Ikegami, Masuhisa Mutsumi, Asuka Maruo, Ozana Mirkovic, Emilia Sorić, Simon Unterajter, Gianmarco Beoni,\r\nTomaz Golub, Adam Harris, Kristian Manev, Ovidiu Muscalu, Kornel Palinko, Dan Rus / Andrej Barbanov, Sebastian Simic, Dunja Zoričić\r\nCarnival: Daria BRDOVNIK Bukvic, Tammy Higgins, Catarina Meneses, Dunja Novkovic, Cristiana Rotolo, Valentina Strok,\r\nAthens Tanovic / Tatjana Andročec, Asuka Mauro, Mutsumi Matsuhisa, Emilia Sorić, Eugen Dobrescu, Tomaz Golub, Adam Harris,\r\nKristian Manev, Ovidiu Muscalu, Kornel Palinko, Sinisa Bosnar / Andrej Barbanov, Gianmarco Beoni, Alen Gotal, Sebastian Simic,\r\nIlinca Barba can, Saya Ikegami, Ozana Mirkovic, Sanda Mouse, Barbara Novković Novak, Rebecaa Smith, Daniel Zobunđija,\r\nDunja Zoricic, Tomaz Golub, Ioan Dumitru Moga, Filip Filipovic'),(4,'Labuđe jezero','Swan lake','20:15:00','22:00:00','14:30:00','18:15:00','10:00:00','30 kuna','Najpoznatiji bijeli balet u 4 čina','Labuđe jezero (ruski: Лебединое озеро) je balet u 4 čina, za koji je glazbu napisao Petar Iljič Čajkovski između 1875. - 1876.\r\nLabuđe jezero danas je možda i najpoznatiji bijeli balet, ali davne veljače 1877. godine u moskovskom Boljšoj teatru, labudi nisu \r\nbili instantan hit. Upravo suprotno, zadao je Petru Iljiču Čajkovskom emocionalni udarac uzrokovan nerazumijevanjem publike, a i \r\nvelikog dijela branše (kako sam izjavljuje – osjećao se posramljeno). Tek 27. siječnja 1895. godine u Marijinskom teatru, kada se \r\nu novoj verziji odlučilo drugačije pristupiti djelu, \'Labuđe jezero\' afirmirano je kao balet koji će bez sumnje zauzeti relevantno mjesto u povijesti.','Ova legenda sastoji se od četiri čina, a priča je sljedeća: Veliki bal na dvoru. Mladom princu Siegfriedu je rođendan i prisiljen \r\nje odrediti koga će uzeti za ženu. Očajan jer se ne može vjenčati iz ljubavi, Siegfried bježi s dvora u šumu, te ugleda jato\r\nlabuda. Vadi luk i strijelu i čeka da slete, no nakon što konačno jedan od labuda to učini, Siegfried shvati da je taj labud\r\nzapravo žena, te se momentalno u nju zaljubi. Žena se zove Odette, koju je zli čarobnjak Von Rothbart zarobio te začarao, tako da\r\nje preko dana labud, a preko noći žena. Ono što je može spasiti je iskrena ljubav, koju joj Siegfried izjavljuje, no u tom trenu se\r\npojavljuje Von Rothbart. Siegfried ga želi ubiti, no Odette ga spriječava, govoreći, ako ubije Von Rothbarta prije nego se\r\nuklone čini, ona će zauvijek ostati labud. Siegfried se zatim vraća u dvorac, a Von Rothbart mu umjesto Odette podmeće svoju kćer\r\nOdile, koja je identična Odetti, no odjevena u crno. Siegfried objavljuje dvoru da je našao ženu, no u tom trenu shvati da to nije Odette. Odette je prokleta da zauvijek ostane labud, te tužni ljubavni par počini samubojstvo, bacivši se u jezero, kojeg čine\r\nsuze njezinih roditelja. Von Rothbart umire, uništen ljubavlju i odanošću nesretnog para.','Kraljica\r\nPrinc Siegfried (njezin sin)\r\nBenno (prinčev prijatelj)\r\nWolfgang (učitelj princa)\r\nOdette (kraljica labudova)\r\nVon Rothbart (opaki čarobnjak koji pretvori Odette u labuda)\r\nOdile (čarobnjakova kći)\r\nostali (labudice, dvorjani, prinčevi prijatelji)','The most famous white ballet in four acts','Swan Lake is a ballet in four acts, for which the music was written by Petar Ilyich Tchaikovsky between the 1875th to 1876th.\r\nSwan Lake is today perhaps the most famous white ballet, but back in February 1877 in Moscow\'s Bolshoi Theatre,\r\nswans were not instantan hit. On the contrary, they gave Petar Ilyich Tchaikovsky emotional impact caused by lack of understanding of the audience, and a large part of the industry (he felt ashamed). \r\nIt was not until 27 January 1895 at the Mariinsky Theatre, when the new version has decided to take a different approach work, \r\nSwan Lake is affirmed as a ballet that will no doubt occupy a relevant place in history.','The legend consists of four acts, and the story is as follows: large ball on the court. \r\nIt is young Prince Siegfried\'s birthday and he is forced to determine who will he take for a wife. \r\nAgonized because they can not marry for love, Siegfried escapes from his house in the woods, and sees a flock swan.\r\nHe draws his bow and arrow and is waiting to swan land, but after the one does, Siegfried realizes that the swan is\r\nactually a woman, and immediately falls in love with her. A woman named Odette, who was captured and bewitched by evil sorcerer\r\nVon Rothbart so that she is the swan overday,but a woman overnight.What can save her is the sincere love, which she says Siegfried,\r\nbut in that moment appears Von Rothbart. Siegfried wants to kill him, but Odette tells him, if he kills Von Rothbart before\r\nremoving the curse, she will forever remain a swan.Siegfried then returned to the castle, and Von Rothbart frame him his daughter\r\nOdile, who is identical to Odette, but dressed in black. Siegfried announces that the court has found a woman, but in that moment\r\nhe realized that it was not Odette. Odette is cursed to forever remain a swan, and sad lover commit suicide, throwing himself into the lake, formed by the tears of her parents. Von Rothbart dies, destroyed by love and loyalty of a unhappy couple.','Queen\r\nPrince Siegfried (her son)\r\nBenno (prince\'s friend)\r\nWolfgang (Prince\'s teacher)\r\nOdette (Queen swans)\r\nVon Rothbart (a wicked sorcerer who transforms Odette into a swan)\r\nOdile (the sorcerer\'s daughter)\r\nothers (trailers, courtiers, princes friends)'),(5,'Zločin i kazna','Crime and Punishment','23:00:00','16:00:00','11:30:00','21:15:00','13:00:00','40 kuna','Predstava o zločinu, krivnji i priznanju, kazni i pokajanju, odgovornosti i posljedicama','Zločin i kazna F. M. Dostojevskog nezaobilazna je postaja u svakom promišljanju o zločinu i njegovoj (ne)opravdanosti,\r\no krivnji i priznanju, kazni i pokajanju, odgovornosti i posljedicama koje smo spremni podnijeti za učinjeno. \r\nJedno od najvećih djela ruske i svjetske književnosti izuzetno je kompleksan i izazovan materijal za svakoga\r\ntko ga poželi oživjeti na pozornici, no vječna priča i danas, 150 godina nakon nastanka, sjaji jednakom magičnom privlačnošću.','Rodion Romanovič Raskoljnikov, propali student prava, potaknut krajnjom bijedom i turobnom budućnošću odlučuje ubiti i opljačkati\r\nAljonu Ivanovnu, omraženu staricu koja lihvarenjem izrabljuje ljude. Osim što ubojstvom planira riješiti vlastite financijske\r\ni obiteljske probleme, smatra ga i etički opravdanim jer, po njegovom mišljenju, životi običnih ljudi koji mu se nalaze na putu ne vrijede ništa spram plemenitih ideala kojima teži; smatra da se on, kao izniman pojedinac (sličan Napoleonu), nalazi iznad moralnih\r\npravila koja obvezuju ostale ljude. Pomno razrađuje plan, ali ipak mu se potkradu pogreške i privlači sumnju policije; i sam \r\npostaje nesiguran glede vlastitih razmišljanja o zločinu te očajava i čezne za iskupljenjem. U psihičkoj krizi kroz koju prolazi\r\npomaže mu prostitutka Sonja Marmeladova, napaćena djevojka koja se ponizno i pasivno drži prema zlu i životnim nedaćama,\r\na utjehu nalazi u kršćanstvu.','Rodion Romanovič Raskoljnikov: Franjo Dijak\r\nArkadij Ivanovič Svidrigajlov: Darko Milas\r\nSofja Semjonovna Marmeladova: Nela Kocsis\r\nAljona Ivanovna: Ingeborg Appelt\r\nLizaveta Ivanovna: Perica Martinović\r\nAvdotja Romanovna Raskoljnikova: Ivana Bolanča\r\nDmitrij Prokofjič Razumihin: Živko Anočić\r\nPorfirij Petrovič: Ozren Grabarić\r\nSemjon Zaharič Marmeladov: Zoran Gogić\r\nKaterina Ivanovna Marmeladova: Anja Šovagović Despot','The play about the crime, guilt and confession, punishment and repentance, accountability and consequences','Crime and Punishment by F. M. Dostoevsky unavoidable stations in any thinking about the crime and its (non) justification,\r\nabout guilt and confession, punishment and repentance, responsibilities and consequences that we are willing to submit after\r\ncommitting a crime. One of the greatest works of Russian and world literature is extremely complex and challenging material for anyone who wants to revive on stage, but the eternal witness and today, 150 years after its creation,\r\nshines with equally magical appeal.','Rodion Romanovich Raskolnikov, a failed law student, driven by extreme misery and dismal future decide to kill and rob\r\nAlyona Ivanovna, a hateful old woman who through usury exploits people. In addition to the murder, he plans to solve his own\r\nfinancial and family issues, believes it is ethically justified because, in his opinion, the lives of ordinary people who are to be\r\nfound along the way are worthless against the noble ideals he pursues; he believes that he, as an exceptional individual\r\n(like Napoleon), is situated above the moral rules that oblige other people. Altought he had carefully elaborated plan, he makes\r\nmistakes and draws suspicion of the police; and he himself is becoming unsure about his own thinking about the crime and despair\r\nand longing for redemption. Throught the psychological crisis he was going, he gets help from a prostitute Sonia Marmeladova,\r\ntroubled girl who is humble and finds solace in Christianity.','Rodion Romanovich Raskolnikov: Franjo Dijak\r\nArkady Ivanovich Svidrigailov: Darko Milas\r\nSofya Semjonovna Marmeladova Nela Kocsis\r\nAlyona Ivanovna: Ingeborg Appelt\r\nLizaveta Ivanovna: Perica Martinović\r\nAvdotja Romanovna Raskolnikov: Ivana Bolanča\r\nDmitry Prokofjič Razumihin: Živko Anočić\r\nPorfiry Petrovich: Ozren Grabarić\r\nSemyon Zaharič Marmeladov: Zoran Gogić\r\nKaterina Ivanovna Marmeladova: Anja Šovagović Despot');

